  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing the `/server.ts` file**\n\nI\'m currently focused on structuring `/server.ts`. I need to set up Express and create the `/api/solve-math` route, utilizing Gemini. I\'m also designing the JSON response format for `/api/solve-math` with a focus on rich structure for a 9:16 Shorts visual player, and understanding what the user would expect.\n\n\n**Considering Creator Personas**\n\nI\'m now thinking about how to make a compelling \"CSAT Math Shorts Solver\". I\'m exploring \"Creator Personas,\" offering users different tones and styles, such as a \"Star Teacher\" or a \"Math Abandoner Savior\". This is meant to make the experience feel more engaging and tailored to individual preferences.\n\n\n**Adding TTS Functionality**\n\nI\'m now integrating text-to-speech using the browser\'s `SpeechSynthesis` API. This offers a lightweight, key-free, and quota-free way to make explanations auditory. I\'m also planning the Shorts structure: a catchy hook, core concept explanation, calculation steps, and a takeaway/cheat key. Additionally, I\'m working on an interactive sandbox, which will give users similar problems to practice with.\n\n\n**Generating New Questions**\n\nI\'m now focused on generating a new practice question with answers, including score tracking and user review notes. I\'m also revising `/server.ts` to include the Gemini image prompt. I need to get the image as a base64 string, then create an imagePart to send to Gemini. I\'m focusing on the JSON structure for the returned value. I want:\n```json\n{\n  \"title\": \"catchy title\",\n  \"difficulty\": \"grade level\",\n  \"concept\": \"math concept\",\n  \"parsedProblemText\": \"transcribed problem text\",\n  \"takeaway\": \"cheat-key/hack\",\n  \"steps\": [{ \"title\": \"step title\", \"explanation\": \"detailed step explanation\" }]\n}\n```\n\n\n**Refining API Response**\n\nI\'m now refining the API response format. I\'m focusing on these fields: `visualFormula`, `explanation`, `accentWords`, and `duration`, all essential for Shorts video creation. I\'m imagining energetic, Creator-style explanations suitable for TTS, highlighting key words. I\'m also planning the `/server.ts` file implementation. I\'m parsing the body size limit for base64 uploads, using Express\'s built-in JSON body parser with a 10MB limit.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the backend entry point `server.ts` to handle the full-stack routing. It will include:\n1. Dynamic route `/api/solve-math` that parses math problem images using the Gemini API and outputs a highly structured, YouTube Shorts-style step-by-step solution.\n2. Lazy initialization of the Gemini SDK client to prevent startup crashes when the API key is not configured yet.\n3. High-quality offline fallback samples so users can test the Shorts generation experience instantly, even if they haven\'t configured their API key yet.\n4. Express static file serving for the React frontend, compatible with both local development and Cloud Run deployment."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 9
      nanos: 741091312
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
