  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Crafting Educational Shorts UI**\n\nI\'m starting to visualize a compelling educational Shorts UI in `src/App.tsx`. The goal is a highly interactive and intuitive design. I\'m focusing on the visual and responsive elements, and on beautiful component organization, including a left panel for problem capture and control. I\'m especially focused on how to make it *pop* for users.\n\n\n**Designing Math Shorts Features**\n\nI\'ve been working on feature implementation. I\'m focusing on math problem image selection, including Korean CSAT presets and upload functionality. I\'m also exploring background themes and sound synchronization modes. I\'m getting exciting with the \"Generate Shorts\" button, especially its interactive loading states and encouraging quotes. The goal is to make a truly engaging math learning experience.\n\n\n**Visualizing New Mobile UI**\n\nI\'m now diving deep into the mobile simulator frame. I\'m focusing on making it look like a real smartphone screen. I\'m especially excited about the progress bar at the top, which will use segment ticks to show step durations, and an Active Step display that features custom typography for the title, a glowing visual formula, and animated subtitles with neon highlighting and staggering pop animations for key words. I\'m also planning to integrate an equalizer for audio visualization and controls for sound cues and TTS.\n\n\n**Adding Interactive Practice Features**\n\nI\'m now integrating crucial features for user engagement! I\'m adding `Prev/Forward` buttons and a custom play speed controller. I\'m especially excited about the \"Cheat-key Banner\" in the bottom panel, summarizing the problem\'s takeaway. The \"Interactive Sandbox Section\" will be key, dynamically generating similar problems with instant feedback, a scoreboard, and animated fireworks. I\'m also exploring `motion/react` for animations.\n\n\n**Implementing UI and Audio**\n\nI\'m now focused on the UI, and will import `motion` from `\"motion/react\"` for animations. I\'m choosing lucide-react icons for UI design, specifically `Upload`, `Play`, `Pause`, `RotateCcw`, `Sparkles`, and more. I plan to maintain a modular `src/App.tsx` file for a clean UI, keeping it under 600 lines. I\'m also exploring a Web Audio API sound synthesizer for study beats and sound cues.\n\n\n**Adding Audio Synths**\n\nI\'m now implementing audio features, specifically a subtle retro chime using `playTransitionBeep` for slide changes, a custom-generated sound synthesized with a Web Audio API, and an \"Ambient Synth Beat\" toggle for background music. My main focus is on a fully user-customizable and responsive auditory experience, while avoiding external audio files. I\'m exploring the `SynthController` class in TypeScript for the audio synthesis.\n\n\n**Refining Sound Synthesis**\n\nI\'m now refining the audio synthesis implementation. I\'m focusing on the `SynthController` class, expanding the methods to include study beats. I\'ve successfully implemented a retro chime for slide transitions and am currently working on a custom study beat generation. I am also working on `startStudyBeats`, and aiming for a customizable auditory experience.\n\n\n**Implementing Lofi Chords**\n\nI\'m now integrating Lofi chord progressions using the Web Audio API. I\'m focusing on synthesizing soft piano chords with a gentle attack and decay, as well as a triangle wave oscillator. I am specifically generating a G minor 7 progression, with the chords being played in sequence, triggered every tick. The goal is to provide a gentle and ambient background music for the user experience.\n\n\n\n**Designing Background Themes**\n\nI\'m now designing background themes for the app. I\'ve outlined a few visual styles: Blackboard with a retro feel, a Cyberpunk aesthetic with neon accents, a Pastel Coral design for a warm feel, and a Graph Notebook theme for a familiar look. I\'m focusing on color palettes and outline styles, aiming for a visual experience that complements the Lofi music, and each other.\n\n\n**Designing UI Grid**\n\nI\'m now focused on generating a grid or canvas using Tailwind\'s background gradients for authentic visual styles. For example, I can make beautiful graph paper using a radial gradient. I\'m also planning to implement speech synthesis using the browser\'s `window.speechSynthesis` for audio explanations with React. I\'ll include callbacks for visual feedback, like a speaker icon.\n\n\n**Adding Math Problem Input**\n\nI\'m now integrating versatile math problem input features. I plan to include packaged Korean CSAT questions as presets with rendered question cards. Also, I\'m especially excited about an interactive canvas where users can upload images, or write custom question text, with a toggle for \"Upload Image\" or \"Directly write text\". This allows instant problem solving! I\'m also ensuring we use Space Grotesk and Inter fonts, as stated in our guidelines.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now update `/src/index.css` to import high-quality Google Fonts (Inter, Space Grotesk, and JetBrains Mono) and set up specialized animations and grid textures for the different aesthetic blackboard, cyberpunk, and mathematical graph paper themes of the Shorts."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 19
      nanos: 364658530
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
