  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Constructing App.tsx**\n\nI\'m starting to build `src/App.tsx` now. My focus is on designing the React layout. I\'ve begun defining the state variables I\'ll need: `imageBase64` for the image data, `mimeType` for its type, and `directText`.\n\n\n**Defining App State**\n\nI\'m now focusing on defining the App\'s state. I\'ve added variables for manual text input, a preset selector (`selectedPreset`), persona, background theme, and generator loading state with progress messages. I also need to track the structured Gemini output and its playback state, including current step index, playing status, speed, and sound settings. Furthermore, I\'ve added flags for TTS, and speaking state.\n\n\n**Adding Sandbox State**\n\nI\'m now integrating the practice sandbox state variables. I\'ve added `practiceQuestion`, `practiceIsLoading`, `selectedAnswer`, `hasCheckedAnswer`, and `sandboxScore` to manage the practice mode. I\'m also considering visually appealing preset selectors, possibly using dynamically generated SVG thumbnails or elegant placeholder text for a template-like feel. I\'m checking the import statements.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now implement a state-of-the-art interactive front-end experience inside `/src/App.tsx` that brings this \354\210\230\353\212\245 \354\210\230\355\225\231 \354\210\217\354\270\240 \355\222\200\354\235\264 \354\240\234\354\236\221\352\270\260 (CSAT Math Shorts Solver) service to life. \n\nIt features:\n1. **Double Input Modes**: File upload for actual handwritten/printed math images, and a backup direct LaTeX/Text editor box.\n2. **Preset templates**: High-quality visual presets for actual legendary CSAT math killer items (Killer item 22 and 15) so the app works beautifully out of the box.\n3. **Responsive Visual Simulator (9:16 Shorts Player)**: Custom designed, styled vertical player with progress tick bars, speed control, transition animations, auto-play, manual rewind, and 4 dynamic themes (Retro Chalkboard, Cyberpunk Neon, Cozy Pastel Rose, Technical Graph Notebook).\n4. **Active Subtitle Highlighting**: Emulates real YouTube Shorts subtitles by highlighting the specific `accentWords` in large, animated typography synchronized with the audio.\n5. **Interactive Web Audio Synth & Sound Cues**: Real-time synthesized low-fi study beats and transition chime sounds to provide full immersion.\n6. **Native Korean Voiceover (SpeechSynthesis TTS)**: An audio speech reader that reads out the creator\'s lines with responsive visual equalizers.\n7. **Active AI Sandbox Practice**: Generates real corresponding multiple-choice practice problems matching the concept of the solved problem, letting users check answers, track scores, and reinforce their learning."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 3
      nanos: 958767742
    }
