  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing UI Improvements**\n\nI\'ve got a great handle on the structural layout of Sections 1, 2, and 3. The current focus is shifting towards \"Immersive UI\" transition, and I\'m currently identifying necessary visual upgrades. The plan is to revamp the outer `min-h-screen` styling, and other things.\n\n\n**Designing Visual Aesthetics**\n\nI\'m currently focused on implementing a modern, glowing design for the header. I\'m exploring rounded curves, borders, and glow effects within the main body. The plan is to transform section containers into dark glass translucent elements using card classes, changing background, border, shadow, and text colors accordingly. I\'m also planning futuristic styling updates for preset buttons, aiming for a glowing blue-purple border for active presets and a dark, rich background using gradients and shadows.\n\n\n**Refining Style Details**\n\nI\'m now diving into the specifics of button and text styling. I\'m focusing on color, borders, and shadows to refine the user interface. I\'m swapping out `border-stone-200` and `bg-stone-100` for white alternatives to enhance the design. Active persona buttons will have a new look, incorporating `border-blue-500` and `bg-blue-500/10` for a clearer visual indicator. I am modifying the background theme selector buttons for an active and inactive state that better fits the modern design.\n\n\n**Implementing UI Components**\n\nI\'m now focusing on specific component styling to align with the evolving Immersive UI. The \"Generate Shorts\" button is getting a vibrant gradient with shadows and hover effects for a visually appealing interaction, mirroring the core design. I\'m also revising the Solution Metadata Board with a frosted glass look, complete with shadows and rounded corners, and refining the Problem Text preview box and Takeaway block styling to better fit the overall design, with gradients and borders. Finally, I\'ll be working on improving the \'Similar Questions\' buttons.\n\n\n**Updating Component Styles**\n\nI\'m now overhauling the practice question components. I\'m focusing on new button styling, gradients, and border colors for a more cohesive Immersive UI. The \"hover\" state styling is being tweaked, swapping `bg-stone-900` for a white alternative. I\'m also revising multiple choice options, adopting a gradient background and bolder text for selected answers. Button colors will be updated to a more modern and fitting palette.\n\n\n**Refining Practice Components**\n\nI\'m currently focused on the practice question styling and related UI elements. I\'m updating specific color schemes. I\'m refining multiple choice selections. Specifically, the \"correct\" and \"incorrect\" feedback are being updated to `bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-900` and `bg-red-500/10 border border-red-500/30 text-red-300`, respectively. I\'m also styling the explanation box with `bg-black/30 border border-white/10 text-white/90` and the next practice button with `border border-white/15 hover:bg-white/5 text-white`. I\'m now transitioning to the right column, specifically the tips card and smartphone simulator, with a shift to glassmorphic aesthetics.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 11
      nanos: 418980003
